This paper deals with the design and analysis of matching mechanisms, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of game theory, artificial intelligence, and algorithms. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses axiomatic methods to characterize and relax strategyproofness, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper provides an algorithm for computing a measure of strategyproofness, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the incentive analysis of non-strategyproof mechanisms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
